1573760,2026-03-31 05:53:27 -0700,2026-03-31 08:13:47 -0700,I need assistance after updating to Firefox ESR,"<p>When I open my Gmail I see the following message:  “This browser version is no longer supported. Please upgrade to a supported browser.” </p><p>So I Downloaded Firefox ESR as suggested by Google and then I moved the Firefox app into my applications folder, but then got the message that ""a newer version already exists, do I want to replace it with the older one I’m moving? Or keep both"", so I kept both. </p><p>However when I go to my application folder I only see one Firefox icon and when I opened my Gmail again I still see that message “This browser version is no longer supported. Please upgrade to a supported browser.” </p><p>I also see that Google is saying that Firefox doesn’t support “offline access to Gmail” what does this mean? </p>",mac-os-x-1013;firefox;esr;,firefox,esr,en-US,1809152;1809157;,atslvdt
