1573661,2026-03-30 18:05:25 -0700,2026-03-30 18:05:25 -0700,Firefox Performance Issue When Playing Letter Boxed,"<p>Hello, </p><p>I’ve been having a performance problem with Firefox that only happens when I play the Letter Boxed web game from the New York Times. </p><p>When I open the puzzle in Firefox (latest version), the letters load fine, but as soon as I start typing, the browser becomes laggy input delays, slow animations, and occasionally the whole tab freezes for a few seconds. I’ve tried the following, but none have fixed it: </p><p>Restarting Firefox Disabling all add-ons Clearing cache and cookies Updating Firefox to the latest version Running in Safe Mode </p><p>Other websites and games work normally, and the issue only appears with this specific NYT game. It also doesn’t happen in other browsers on the same machine. </p><p>System Info: ‑ OS: Windows 10 ‑ Firefox Version: (latest stable) ‑ RAM: 16 GB ‑ CPU: Intel i5 </p><p>Questions: </p><p>Is this a known issue with Firefox and the Letter Boxed game? Are there specific settings (hardware acceleration, graphics) that I should adjust? How can I troubleshoot what is causing the lag within Firefox? </p><p>Any help would be greatly appreciated thanks in advance! </p>",windows-11;firefox;app-responsiveness;,firefox,app-responsiveness,en-US,"",williamfarah65
